column11: Embryos were flushed at E3.75 from uterine horns using flushing using M2. The zona pellucida was removed using acid Tyrode’s solution. Embryos were subjected to immunosurgery. Single-cell dissociation of ICMs was performed in a 1:1 mixture of Accutase and 0.025% trypsin plus 1% chick serum.
column12: Mice used were intercrosses of PDGFRa::H2B-GFP/+, in which a cassette containing human H2B fused to enhanced green protein (H2B-GFP) was targeted to the Pdgfra locus, and first filial generation (F1) hybrids (C57BL/6JxCBA/J) (Charles River). All embryos used in this study were obtained from natural mating.
column14: Dissociated single cells were transferred immediately into Smart-Seq2 single-cell lysis buffer and immediately frozen on dry ice.
column15: Smart-Seq2 library was prepared as described in Picelli S et al. 2014.
